column5: ...will always be wet, now that this has begun...     She's just a year old and has been hesitant of the water until just lately.
Hahahaha, I got a good laugh out of this.  At least you'll have some good times/memories out of the deal.

I'm guessing Black Lab...right    ???  Because I love Labs and Chesapeake's but they are a bit large for my house.....came this close "-" to getting my new buddy this past winter....a Chocolate Lab female that I really wanted but someone just BARELY beat me to the punch....maybe this fall it will happen..  But anyways....NICE LOOKING WATER BUDDY you have there and LOTS of future memories in the making. Bob
Thanks Bob.  Moosy is actually a labrador/golden retreiver cross.  She's not too big at about 65 lbs, she'll always seem small to me, my last dog was a massive beast.
Hey Mines the exact same cross, golden and retriever. Loves the water twice as much as any dog i ever owned, and smart as all get out too. Here is Trinity, my girl
Every time some one yells "fish on" or "got em", my peanut is in the water chasing the fish. Woul not have it any other way.
I hate to tell you Merc, but I think you been harboring a black wolf all these years.....
